headline: Near a 52-Week Low, 3 Reasons Why This Dividend King Is a No-Brainer Buy for Reliable Passive Income
summary: Procter & Gamble stock has sold off along with the broader consumer staples sector.  The consumer goods giant has a fairly flexible supply chain despite being such a large business.  P&G has a sizeable capital return program and an ultra-reliable dividend.
